I wouldn't do this.

02:28.849 --> 02:30.658
It's a Pan flute, OK?
I'll take care of it.

02:30.670 --> 02:31.383
Why is he here?

02:31.385 --> 02:34.286
Hey, Tom? Tom, you mind?

02:34.288 --> 02:38.490
W-We're honored.
Thank you, sir, but we're good. Thank you.

02:40.227 --> 02:42.227
- He's not stopping.
- He's not stopping.

02:42.229 --> 02:43.795
- OK. Go get him. Go.
- Oh, my God.

02:43.797 --> 02:46.498
- He's not stopping.
- Hey, Tom. Tom, friend.

02:46.500 --> 02:49.434
- Dad would have loved a bagpiper.
- Yeah. Yeah.

02:54.475 --> 02:57.910
Give us your poor, your
tired, your huddled masses

02:57.912 --> 03:00.612
yearning to be free,
your Mexicans

03:00.614 --> 03:04.249
yearning for handouts
and entitlements

03:04.251 --> 03:07.352
and free food and bus passes.

03:07.354 --> 03:09.588
I can't stop him. You stop him.

03:09.590 --> 03:13.625
- Mexicans. Mexicans, God bless us.
- Dad. Dad, stop it.

03:13.627 --> 03:16.929
I say put hinges
on that goddamn wall.

03:16.931 --> 03:21.733
Dad. The Diegos live next door.
OK? You're being offensive.

03:21.735 --> 03:23.569
Half of them are undocumented.

03:23.571 --> 03:26.405
Papers.<i> Documentos.</i>
Pay,<i> por favor.</i>

03:26.407 --> 03:27.940
You are a racist son of a bitch.

03:27.942 --> 03:30.442
I am, I am,
and I need another drink.

03:30.444 --> 03:31.132
Great.

03:31.144 --> 03:33.245
Well, we seem to have
silenced the neighborhood.

03:33.247 --> 03:35.214
Happy Fourth of July.

03:41.288 --> 03:42.588
Everyone ready?

03:43.424 --> 03:44.756
- Sure.
- How do I look?

03:44.758 --> 03:47.359
- You look great.
- Great. You look good.

03:47.361 --> 03:50.562
I don't remember what I'm supposed to do.
I'm just... I'm very...

03:50.564 --> 03:53.298
I'm very nervous,
and I can't stop shaking.

03:53.300 --> 03:54.866
What we do, we wait for
the music to start.

03:54.868 --> 03:58.403
Then we walk down the aisle,
and then Eddie gives the eulogy.

03:58.405 --> 04:00.239
Eddie? I'm sorry.
I thought it was Andy.

04:00.241 --> 04:02.407
- Oh, I was ready to, but...
- No.

04:02.409 --> 04:04.943
Bob wanted Eddie
to do the eulogy.

04:04.945 --> 04:08.313
- Edward, you will do the eulogy.
- Yes.

04:09.283 --> 04:11.250
I'll keep it short and sweet.

04:13.520 --> 04:14.720
You all right?

04:16.257 --> 04:18.624
Welcome to this celebration

04:18.625 --> 04:20.759
of the joining
of Robert Joseph Mills

04:20.761 --> 04:22.928
with our lord, our God.

04:22.930 --> 04:25.931
Edward has some thoughts he'd like to
share with us before the Mass begins.

04:25.933 --> 04:28.600
If you're not Catholic,
feel free to come up during Communion.

04:28.602 --> 04:32.638
Just please cross your arms,
and you can receive a blessing.

04:32.640 --> 04:35.674
However, do not partake
in the sacrament.

04:36.810 --> 04:37.843
Welcome, all.

04:41.315 --> 04:43.615
Thank you, Father.

04:45.486 --> 04:50.522
Hi, everybody. Great turnout,
Dad would have liked that. Um...

04:52.526 --> 04:55.627
It just...
It feels funny that he's not here.

04:55.629 --> 04:58.597
I wanna talk to him.
Here, he's got to be down here.

04:59.933 --> 05:03.468
Sorry, just...
I'm gonna bring him down.

05:03.470 --> 05:04.903
I hope it doesn't
offend anybody.

05:08.008 --> 05:10.375
I just...
The Church doesn't like this.

05:10.377 --> 05:13.945
I know the Catholic Church
wants him to stay in the back.

05:13.947 --> 05:15.914
And he only comes in
during the Mass.

05:15.916 --> 05:19.418
That's what they told us,
and I...

05:19.420 --> 05:22.387
I'm not really Catholic anymore.
I mean, I wasn't confirmed.

05:22.389 --> 05:24.356
So I just wanted him
down here, no offense.

05:24.358 --> 05:26.591
Just want to talk to him.
I'm sorry.

05:27.895 --> 05:29.594
Um, yeah.

05:30.931 --> 05:32.331
That feels better.

05:33.801 --> 05:37.869
Well, death is horrible.

05:39.707 --> 05:43.475
Man, we've been through
something, haven't we? Oh, gosh.

05:43.477 --> 05:45.544
It went on and on and on.

05:48.716 --> 05:49.732
Let me tell you.

05:49.733 --> 05:50.749
This man is a fighter.

05:56.423 --> 05:58.490
Hey, great job on the...

05:59.760 --> 06:01.960
- Color.
- OK.

06:01.962 --> 06:04.496
Color or black and white?

06:04.498 --> 06:07.566
Color is more expensive. Dad looks
pretty good in black and white, right?

06:07.568 --> 06:08.967
Zak, Zak, Zak,
we aren't there yet.

06:08.969 --> 06:11.570
We haven't still got
the order for the liturgy.

06:11.572 --> 06:13.105
Eddie, how's the eulogy coming?

06:13.107 --> 06:16.475
Um, well, listen, folks,
we have priorities tonight.

06:16.477 --> 06:19.845
Semifinals,<i> Idol,</i>
is on right now!

06:19.847 --> 06:22.414
Oh, my God,
that pigtailed country girl?

06:22.416 --> 06:23.949
I like what she's cookin'.

06:23.951 --> 06:25.784
You like her boobs,
if that's what you mean.

06:25.786 --> 06:28.086
She's good.
That fat black girl, she's fantastic.

06:28.088 --> 06:29.521
She's gonna win it.

06:29.523 --> 06:30.989
The pigtails, the
boobs, and the voice.

06:30.991 --> 06:32.724
Sorry, that's just how it is.

06:32.726 --> 06:34.793
If you're fat on <i> Idol,</i>
you're gonna win.

06:34.795 --> 06:36.828
Could we stop
with the fat, please?

06:36.830 --> 06:39.765
Guys. We've got to finish
the service in the next hour.

06:41.502 --> 06:44.469
- Jesus. Sorry, Dad.
- Oh, fuck!

06:44.471 --> 06:46.538
Can we watch it
with the F-bombs, please?

06:46.540 --> 06:50.709
You don't wing a fu...
A eulogy, Eddie.

06:50.711 --> 06:52.577
Too many people
are counting on you.

06:52.579 --> 06:53.945
I think I'm gonna wing it.

06:54.848 --> 06:56.181
Father Rose called,

06:56.183 --> 06:57.716
and he wants to see the eulogy

06:57.718 --> 07:00.018
so he can refer to it
for the homily.

07:00.020 --> 07:02.154
"Father Rose sat on a tack.
Father Rose."

07:02.156 --> 07:05.991
OK. OK. I think,
we're all probably pretty low blood sugar.

07:05.993 --> 07:08.660
- So, here we go.
- -Oh, what do we have here?

07:08.662 --> 07:10.629
We have some
delicious sandwiches.

07:10.631 --> 07:12.898
- I've reached Uber Lord Warrior.
- Jay, get off that, please.

07:12.900 --> 07:14.900
It's three echelons above
Black Death Swamp Field.

07:14.902 --> 07:16.635
Did you hear what I said?
Please get off that.

07:16.637 --> 07:18.770
That's until the Black
Death Swamp, right there,

07:18.772 --> 07:20.872
- seeps into an open orifice.
- Oh!

07:20.874 --> 07:23.642
- OK. Enough. Off with that, please!
- Have you seen this?

07:23.644 --> 07:25.710
- These are great, Diane.
- Yes, I've seen it.

07:25.712 --> 07:27.679
- Please. Off.
- My immunity crystal broke.

07:27.681 --> 07:29.047
- You suck.
- Shit.

07:29.049 --> 07:30.949
All right,
what have we got here?

07:30.951 --> 07:34.019
Right here is a vegan surprise,
and it's a cheese steak,

07:34.021 --> 07:38.056
but with hummus and a quinoa
paste which is delicious.

07:38.058 --> 07:42.661
Ooh, and then this one.
Diet, gluten-free Chicken Caesar Wrap.

07:42.663 --> 07:44.963
Huh. I didn't know
that you were vegan.

07:44.965 --> 07:46.531
She is so not.

07:46.533 --> 07:48.200
Attitude and tone, please.

07:48.202 --> 07:50.669
I get them from
Pick-a-Deli-Square.

07:50.671 --> 07:53.104
My Curves trainer is the one
that set me up with them.

07:53.106 --> 07:55.507
- Well, I'm sorry to hear that.
- Funny. Hilarious.

07:55.509 --> 07:58.510
She eats chocolate pretzels every
night, but that's OK, right, Mom?

08:02.583 --> 08:04.983
This family is so judgmental.

08:04.985 --> 08:07.118
I would have made
a delicious family dinner,

08:07.120 --> 08:10.055
but my father just died,
and I'm mourning him, all right?

08:10.057 --> 08:12.924
Diane, I didn't ask you
to cook, OK? This is fine.

08:12.926 --> 08:14.759
- This is great.
- It is fine.

08:14.761 --> 08:16.828
And don't expect waffles
and eggs tomorrow.

08:16.830 --> 08:19.164
- Just cereal, all right?
- Do you want waffles and eggs?

08:19.166 --> 08:21.132
- Just cereal...
- No, we didn't...

08:21.134 --> 08:23.969
Minus the Black Death,
if that's all right with you, Jay!

08:23.971 --> 08:25.904
You suck.

08:27.908 --> 08:29.741
I'm processing!

08:30.711 --> 08:31.743
Fuck!

08:32.679 --> 08:34.712
No, you...

08:34.715 --> 08:38.049
No, just let him go.
He'll be fine.

08:39.253 --> 08:43.955
You know, as devout a Catholic

08:43.957 --> 08:46.958
as Dad was,
he didn't want to go to heaven.

08:48.729 --> 08:51.963
He did not...
want to meet Jesus.

08:51.965 --> 08:54.032
No, he fought...

08:55.035 --> 08:57.135
every day in that hospital.

08:57.137 --> 09:01.673
He fought to stay here.
He wanted another day...

09:01.675 --> 09:04.175
on Earth. Didn't you, Dad?

09:04.177 --> 09:05.677
He wanted another day with you.

09:07.114 --> 09:08.713
He loved you.

09:09.550 --> 09:14.119
He wanted...
my God, a steamed crab.

09:14.121 --> 09:17.155
You know, he wanted a cold beer.

09:17.157 --> 09:20.926
He wanted another day at the beach.
He wanted to walk down that boardwalk.

09:23.997 --> 09:26.064
You know, at the end,
he just wanted...

09:27.034 --> 09:29.167
just another sip of water.

09:29.169 --> 09:31.970
And I wish I could have
given it to him, ya know?

09:32.973 --> 09:36.641
He just wanted one more.
One more breath.

09:44.151 --> 09:45.650
Wow.

09:51.625 --> 09:54.125
Wow. That looks good.

09:56.797 --> 09:59.864
You still doing
the valet thing in Chicago?

09:59.866 --> 10:02.934
I'm a doorman, Dad,
at the Peninsula.

10:02.936 --> 10:06.204
It's a five-star hotel.
It's a pretty big deal.

10:06.206 --> 10:08.306
I told you
get a civil service job.

10:08.308 --> 10:10.175
You never have
to worry about a thing.

10:10.177 --> 10:12.010
Secure. Go for the security.

10:12.012 --> 10:14.813
Security. Yes, sir.
Join the Army.

10:17.718 --> 10:20.085
I fought for my country.
I was half your age.

10:20.087 --> 10:23.622
I stayed in the service
just to sock some cash away.

10:23.624 --> 10:24.823
- Nothing wrong with that.
- Yeah.

10:24.825 --> 10:26.691
Dad, it was
the Vietnam War, remember?

10:26.693 --> 10:30.028
You were drafted,
so I don't really think you had a choice.

10:30.030 --> 10:32.797
When you grow up
with very little,

10:32.799 --> 10:35.233
you learn to appreciate the
security the Army gives you.

10:35.235 --> 10:40.972
Dad, you and I both know I never would
have made it in the fucking Army.

10:43.143 --> 10:47.145
I would have given my left nut
to really... really be an artist,

10:47.147 --> 10:51.116
but we had you kids,
and I had to step up, you know?

10:51.118 --> 10:53.051
A struggling cartoonist?

10:53.053 --> 10:55.654
I mean, you can't feed four mouths.
Forget about it.

10:55.656 --> 10:59.924
Oh, yeah, life is full
of disappointment.

10:59.926 --> 11:02.327
"You're never gonna
get what you want."

11:02.329 --> 11:05.263
You used to tell us
that, Dad, right?

11:06.867 --> 11:08.266
What the hell is this all
about, anyway?

11:08.268 --> 11:10.301
- Nothing, I just said...
- What's up your ass?

11:10.303 --> 11:12.270
Whatever you didn't achieve,
whatever disappointments that you had,

11:12.272 --> 11:13.672
that's your own.

11:13.674 --> 11:14.839
Regrets? I have
no goddamn regrets.

11:14.841 --> 11:16.441
Oh, come on. That's bullshit.

11:16.443 --> 11:18.743
I don't know what the hell
you're talking about, regrets.

11:18.745 --> 11:22.013
Well, look around! The art.

11:22.015 --> 11:24.082
This is what gave you joy.
You're an artist.

11:24.084 --> 11:26.284
You will never understand
that kind of responsibility.

11:26.286 --> 11:29.354
Those kids standing there, looking at you.
"What are you gonna do, Dad?"

11:29.356 --> 11:31.156
It's just you.

11:31.158 --> 11:34.359
Kids. Boom, boom, boom, boom.
There they are.

11:34.361 --> 11:36.461
Feed 'em. Take care of 'em.

11:36.463 --> 11:40.799
Your life is looking at your own
face in the mirror, what the hell?

11:42.035 --> 11:43.435
It's not the same thing, is it?

11:43.437 --> 11:46.037
Because I'm not a dad,
I don't know?

11:46.039 --> 11:49.174
You have to admit,
my friend, you...

11:49.176 --> 11:50.875
You took the low road.

11:50.877 --> 11:52.110
Oh, my God. Well, that's...

11:52.112 --> 11:54.746
You and your whole
goddamn generation.

11:54.748 --> 11:56.381
"Me, me, what do I want?"

11:56.383 --> 11:59.417
I've worked hard ever
since I was 12 years old,

11:59.419 --> 12:01.753
every fucking day,
and you know it.

12:01.755 --> 12:04.089
I've been retired for 24 years.

12:04.091 --> 12:07.859
I work harder now than I ever
did in my life. You see all this?

12:07.861 --> 12:09.794
Where do you think it came from?

12:09.796 --> 12:13.398
It came from my work.
Work! I lived, Eddie.

12:13.400 --> 12:15.233
I'm waiting for
the other part, Dad.

12:16.369 --> 12:18.803
Come on.
I know you want to say it.

12:18.805 --> 12:23.074
I haven't accomplished
anything with my life.

12:23.076 --> 12:24.943
Isn't that what you want to say?

12:27.948 --> 12:29.214
Son...

12:29.215 --> 12:30.481
you're drinking a beer
in the afternoon.

12:30.484 --> 12:32.751
You offered it to me.

12:34.221 --> 12:39.891
Whenever I drink a beer at night,
it's because I've earned it.

12:39.893 --> 12:41.526
You got to build a life, Eddie.

12:41.528 --> 12:43.962
Brick by brick.
You got to build it.

12:43.964 --> 12:47.098
What are you saying?
I didn't fucking earn this beer?

12:47.100 --> 12:50.535
Notre Dame just intercepted
on the five-yard line.

12:50.537 --> 12:52.303
They are going to score.
Come on. Come on.

12:52.305 --> 12:55.306
- I forgot about the game.
- Notre Dame. Go, go.

12:55.308 --> 12:57.108
I'll be right there.

13:04.785 --> 13:07.385
I kind of, um, forgot
what I was gonna say.

13:10.023 --> 13:12.457
Andy, you want to say something?

13:12.459 --> 13:15.059
Yeah, sure, Eddie. Yeah.

13:15.896 --> 13:17.195
Hi, everybody.

13:17.197 --> 13:19.998
I just, uh, happen
to have some notes.

13:20.000 --> 13:25.804
Here. I'm so grateful to God
that Dad was our father.

13:25.806 --> 13:29.240
Because he...
He was also our hero.

13:29.242 --> 13:32.010
He taught us how to be tough

13:32.012 --> 13:34.112
and to stand up
for what we believed in,

13:34.114 --> 13:36.080
and he always supported us,

13:36.082 --> 13:39.918
because he taught us that life is
tough, and you have to be tough.

13:39.920 --> 13:43.288
Because life is scary.
It's not all peace and love,

13:43.290 --> 13:46.324
and everybody doesn't
always win a trophy.

13:46.326 --> 13:47.992
And you got to be tough.

13:47.994 --> 13:50.528
And you got to be a man.
And that was my dad.

13:50.530 --> 13:53.164
I remember when I was came
home from school one day,

13:53.166 --> 13:55.500
and a school bully
had called me fat,

13:55.502 --> 13:57.602
and I was upset, and I told Dad.

13:57.604 --> 13:59.904
And he said,
"You turn your butt around,

13:59.906 --> 14:03.341
you go back to that school, and you
punch that slob right in the nose."

14:03.343 --> 14:06.277
And I knew my dad loved me,
even if he never said it,

14:06.279 --> 14:08.179
because then he gave me
a big hug.

14:08.181 --> 14:11.349
And my dad... my dad's hugs, man,

14:11.351 --> 14:15.286
he gave us those big bearhugs,
you know, didn't he, Diane?

14:15.288 --> 14:18.623
He gave us all the bearhugs,
Right? He... Zak? Eddie?

14:18.625 --> 14:21.359
He gave us bearhugs, 'cause he loved
us, and he was tough.

14:21.361 --> 14:24.195
My dad was a tough guy.
He was a man.

14:24.197 --> 14:27.365
He was tough,
and he didn't need to say he loved us.

14:27.367 --> 14:33.004
We knew it, and he gave us
hugs, and he was a good man.

14:35.508 --> 14:37.275
Thanks, buddy.

14:38.345 --> 14:40.645
I'll just...
I'll put it back now,

14:40.647 --> 14:42.113
Then you can start.

14:42.115 --> 14:44.282
I'll put it right back. OK.

14:45.652 --> 14:47.085
There we go.

14:51.491 --> 14:53.992
Oh, no, jeez. I'm sorry.

14:53.994 --> 14:55.226
All right. It's OK.

14:57.497 --> 14:58.497
Sorry.

15:00.200 --> 15:02.467
All right. I think we're good.
Father.

15:09.609 --> 15:12.176
When's the last time I've been to a Mass?
I don't know.

15:12.178 --> 15:15.146
- You should read it.
- I really don't...

15:15.148 --> 15:17.081
- They want me to read this.
- OK.

15:18.218 --> 15:22.086
Ah! "Intercession Prayers:
In Baptism, Robert Mills"

15:22.088 --> 15:23.454
receive the light of Christ.

15:23.456 --> 15:24.923
Scatter the darkness now,

15:24.925 --> 15:27.625
"and lead him over
the waters of death."

15:27.627 --> 15:29.527
That's very poetic.

15:29.529 --> 15:30.662
Further down.

15:30.664 --> 15:32.230
Uh, "For the sick and dying."

15:32.232 --> 15:33.665
May they find peace
in their suffering."

15:33.667 --> 15:35.700
- That's fine.
- Mm-hmm.

15:35.702 --> 15:37.302
Wait a minute.

15:38.571 --> 15:40.471
"For the unborn?

15:40.473 --> 15:43.238
- "Pray for their mothers
to choose life over death?"

15:43.250 --> 15:44.175
- Unborn?

15:44.177 --> 15:47.011
Yeah, yeah. This is it.

15:47.013 --> 15:49.213
- Yeah.
- Are you kidding me with this?

15:49.215 --> 15:51.282
- What?
- You'd have actually put this in the Mass?

15:51.284 --> 15:53.318
It's what Dad wanted.
He was very pro-life.

15:53.320 --> 15:55.653
We thought the ceremony should
reflect Dad's religious experience.

15:55.655 --> 15:57.155
Right. Right.

15:57.157 --> 15:58.356
My parish says a prayer

15:58.358 --> 16:00.058
for aborted babies every Sunday,

16:00.060 --> 16:01.426
- so they go to heaven.
- I don't care.

16:01.428 --> 16:02.660
So, pro-life Democrats

16:02.662 --> 16:03.695
are all gonna just burn in hell?

16:03.697 --> 16:05.029
Oh, my gosh, I knew you guys

16:05.031 --> 16:06.297
would make this about politics.

16:06.299 --> 16:08.166
Where is the word Democrat
anywhere in there?

16:08.168 --> 16:10.168
You're completely
politicizing Dad's funeral.

16:10.170 --> 16:11.569
This has absolutely nothing
to do with politics,

16:11.571 --> 16:13.438
- all right?
- Oh, it does.

16:13.440 --> 16:15.640
<i>Roe v. Wade</i> is going to be overturned.
Deal with it!

16:15.642 --> 16:18.042
- It's not going to be overturned.
- That's a political stance.

16:18.044 --> 16:20.078
- Why do you always go there?
- Over my dead body.

16:20.080 --> 16:22.714
I don't want to interrupt.
I'm sorry, but you want to go soon?

16:22.716 --> 16:24.349
Oh, yeah. Yeah, we will.

16:24.351 --> 16:27.318
- Come on over.
- I'm just... I'm tired.

16:27.320 --> 16:30.088
I know, baby.
It's been a tough day.

16:30.090 --> 16:32.323
I don't know...

16:32.325 --> 16:37.061
I don't know whether... what
people wear to be cremated,

16:37.063 --> 16:40.732
because this is
his favorite suit, but...

16:40.734 --> 16:43.267
he loved other things, too.

16:43.269 --> 16:46.270
- Loved the one that...
- When he wears the one...

16:46.272 --> 16:49.440
Oh, no, no, no,
you have to let the doggies out.

16:49.442 --> 16:52.477
- OK. We will. We will.
- We'll take care of it.

16:52.479 --> 16:55.213
You'll be all right.

16:55.215 --> 16:57.181
Your dad's been very organized.

16:57.183 --> 16:59.350
I won't have to
worry about a thing.

17:00.353 --> 17:02.286
Why are we even
talking about this?

17:02.288 --> 17:04.288
I don't want to be
a burden on anybody, OK?

17:04.290 --> 17:06.124
And you should all know this.

17:06.126 --> 17:07.492
Look, I'm not getting
any younger,

17:07.493 --> 17:09.727
and I probably won't
get much older either.

17:09.729 --> 17:12.329
And, um, your dad's
gonna be cremated.

17:12.332 --> 17:16.034
- I just want you to know.
- Wow. Cremation?

17:16.036 --> 17:18.102
Wow. Great topic for lunch.

17:18.104 --> 17:20.405
- Look...
- And he doesn't want a viewing either.

17:20.406 --> 17:22.373
Hey, look, it's what I want.

17:22.375 --> 17:24.776
Isn't that right, sweetheart?
You don't want a viewing?

17:24.778 --> 17:26.778
So, don't blame me, any of you.

17:26.780 --> 17:28.512
Really? Why is that, Dad?

17:28.515 --> 17:32.817
Your stepmother doesn't like
being surprised or scared.

17:32.819 --> 17:35.720
Ah, come on, a viewing
is creepy, anyway.

17:35.722 --> 17:40.091
Well, the reason you have a viewing
is so people can pay their respects.

17:40.093 --> 17:42.193
Oh, come on with this.

17:42.195 --> 17:45.663
Your family can have time to process
the loss before jumping into a funeral.

17:45.665 --> 17:48.766
Look she doesn't want it, OK?
That's good enough for me.

17:48.768 --> 17:51.135
I owe my whole life
to this woman.

17:51.137 --> 17:52.270
That's right.

17:52.272 --> 17:54.238
I can't stand surprises.

17:54.240 --> 17:56.541
That's why I always read
the books backwards.

17:56.543 --> 17:59.710
Hold it. You read the
endings of books first?

17:59.712 --> 18:02.480
Yes, I do.
I read the last page first,

18:02.482 --> 18:06.350
because if I don't know the
ending, I get very, very anxious.

18:06.352 --> 18:07.752
- I never knew that.
- Me neither.

18:07.754 --> 18:09.420
Very interesting.

18:09.422 --> 18:12.490
Dad, a viewing is not
about you. It's for us,

18:12.492 --> 18:14.525
the people left behind
who are still grieving.

18:14.527 --> 18:16.494
Can you imagine Dawn
staring down at me?

18:16.496 --> 18:20.832
I'm cold in the coffin, like this...
Stop.

18:20.834 --> 18:22.834
She would have that last
image of me haunting her,

18:22.836 --> 18:25.269
thinking I'm gonna rise up
out of the coffin like...

18:26.739 --> 18:28.573
Stop it, Bob.

18:32.479 --> 18:34.412
Oh, no.
Abner and Dusty, no, wait.

18:34.414 --> 18:37.715
Wait. Dusty. No, no, no, no, no.
Come on. Come on.

18:37.717 --> 18:39.450
They're stealing the...

18:39.452 --> 18:41.452
Pickles. He loves pickles.
Give him a pickle.

18:41.454 --> 18:43.470
Come here, sweetheart.
Come here, baby boy.

18:43.482 --> 18:44.188
Knock it off.

18:44.190 --> 18:46.624
- Knock it off, the two of you.
- Go on. Sit down.

18:46.626 --> 18:50.294
Sit down. Be quiet.
That's right. Look at me.

18:51.131 --> 18:52.296
All right.

18:53.700 --> 18:55.266
Dad, you're looking slim.

18:55.268 --> 18:58.669
Lost three notches on the belt.

18:58.671 --> 19:00.204
Not bad, huh?

19:00.206 --> 19:03.207
- Thank you.
- I listen to the old boss.

19:03.209 --> 19:07.245
- Low sodium, no sugar. Portion control.
- There you go.

19:07.247 --> 19:10.481
- He's lost 18 pounds.
- Hey!

19:10.483 --> 19:13.217
Remind me, honey.
We have to get more fish oil supplements

19:13.219 --> 19:17.522
on the way back from your eye exam
on Friday. We'll get it at Costco.

19:17.524 --> 19:20.758
Your father doesn't
burn enough calories

19:20.760 --> 19:22.627
without exercise anymore.

19:22.629 --> 19:24.896
He can't go on his cardio
walks with me at all.

19:24.898 --> 19:29.400
I just can't breathe. I told her
take the dogs, do it without me.

19:29.402 --> 19:32.370
And Bernie, Bernie's a good man.
He can keep up with her.

19:32.372 --> 19:33.804
Who's this Bernie?

19:33.806 --> 19:36.374
Oh, he's four houses down.

19:36.376 --> 19:38.643
He's that beautiful house
with holly and roses.

19:38.645 --> 19:41.512
I help him with his Greyhound
Rescue every other Sunday.

19:41.514 --> 19:44.215
Bernie is a...
He's a good-looking man.

19:44.217 --> 19:47.418
He's got salt-and-pepper
hair, and he's tall.

19:47.420 --> 19:49.587
And, yeah, he's really handsome.

19:49.589 --> 19:51.322
Mmm. That's Bernie.

19:53.259 --> 19:56.527
Well, I can't give up
my workouts.

19:56.529 --> 19:59.564
- Dad, I had no idea you weren't walking.
- Yeah.

19:59.566 --> 20:02.533
Until we get to the bottom of
this breathing problem, you know?

20:02.535 --> 20:05.670
Yeah, the cardiologist
thinks it's emphysema.

20:05.672 --> 20:08.506
The pulmonary specialist
thinks it's his heart.

20:08.508 --> 20:12.677
Just pray it's not emphysema.

20:12.679 --> 20:15.680
When this man turned 73,
he started falling apart.

20:17.984 --> 20:20.751
Listen, he's the Bionic Man.
What have you got inside there?

20:20.753 --> 20:24.922
You've got a pacemaker,
two valve replacements.

20:24.924 --> 20:26.857
- How many stents you got?
- Five.

20:26.859 --> 20:29.227
- Five.
- They don't last forever.

20:31.497 --> 20:34.865
Diane, those pounds seem
to be sneaking up on you.

20:34.867 --> 20:36.634
Do you ever
get your thyroid checked?

20:38.671 --> 20:40.238
Not recently, Dawn.

20:40.240 --> 20:42.907
Well, I always get
my thyroid checked,

20:42.909 --> 20:45.543
especially when my clothes
are getting a little tight.

20:46.846 --> 20:49.714
Well, maybe I should just
get my jaw wired shut.

20:53.453 --> 20:54.569
Oh, that's an option.

20:54.570 --> 20:55.686
Oh. Oh, you were kidding.

20:56.689 --> 20:58.322
Wow, I'm so sorry.

21:03.263 --> 21:06.330
Spit.

21:06.332 --> 21:07.698
OK.

21:08.868 --> 21:10.034
- Hey, guys.
- Eddie!

21:10.036 --> 21:12.536
Oh, hey, Eddie!

21:12.538 --> 21:14.505
What's this, huh?

21:14.507 --> 21:16.807
I told you on Monday
Eddie was flying in.

21:16.809 --> 21:20.311
He's on so many meds right now,
he can't remember anything.

21:20.313 --> 21:21.712
Nobody told me anything.

21:21.714 --> 21:23.014
Oh, yes, I did.

21:23.016 --> 21:25.283
I must really be in
trouble with you here.

21:25.285 --> 21:27.385
- No. Hi.
- Hi.

21:27.387 --> 21:28.635
Oh, you smell like smoke.

21:28.647 --> 21:30.888
You should be working.
It's a waste of time.

21:30.890 --> 21:32.890
- All I'm doing is sitting here...
- Dad, I was coming anyway.

21:32.892 --> 21:34.058
Getting needles
for Christ sakes.

21:34.060 --> 21:35.860
- I was coming anyway. OK?
- Yeah. Sure.

21:35.862 --> 21:37.862
- You look good.
- Good to see you.

21:37.864 --> 21:39.864
Thanks. I appreciate it.
They're poking me.

21:39.866 --> 21:42.333
They're sticking needles
every place you can think of.

21:42.335 --> 21:45.403
Wow, that looks
like it really smarts, huh?

21:45.405 --> 21:47.505
Heard you missed your flight.

21:47.507 --> 21:49.507
I did. It's a whole story.
It's not important.

21:49.509 --> 21:52.777
- So, you wanna eat?
- Not necessarily.

21:52.779 --> 21:55.379
Well, Andy and Diane are downstairs
at the commissary if you want...

21:55.381 --> 21:56.781
If you're hungry,
you can just...

21:56.783 --> 21:58.516
They're all downstairs
eating lunch.

21:58.518 --> 21:59.784
You're staying
at Diane's, right?

21:59.786 --> 22:01.852
- Yeah.
- There's nothing to do up here.

22:01.854 --> 22:03.854
Might as well go down there and say hello.
I'll tell you,

22:03.856 --> 22:06.624
that 695 is gonna be a shit
show in a couple of hours.

22:06.626 --> 22:08.492
If you want to get going,
now's the time.

22:08.494 --> 22:10.761
Dad. I just got here. I'm not
getting back on the beltway.

22:10.763 --> 22:13.731
You know what happened to me last night?
I couldn't sleep a wink.

22:13.733 --> 22:17.034
Yeah, Abner had diarrhea everywhere
at 1:00 a.m. in the morning.

22:17.036 --> 22:18.769
Sprayed with his tail.
It was unbelievable.

22:18.771 --> 22:20.805
She spent all night cleaning
the carpets for that damn dog.

22:20.807 --> 22:22.344
Dr. Brewster continually
wants us to go on kibble.

22:22.356 --> 22:22.940
He eats too fast,

22:22.942 --> 22:24.775
and he eats too much,
and he's old like me.

22:24.777 --> 22:26.410
He can't eat kibble
without gravy.

22:26.412 --> 22:28.479
You love that dog.
You love that dog.

22:28.481 --> 22:30.448
Oh, come on. You love that dog.

22:30.450 --> 22:32.088
That guy charges as much
as these guys charge here.

22:32.100 --> 22:32.650
You love it.

22:32.652 --> 22:35.119
Hey, you know what?
Maybe I will just let Diane know I'm here.

22:35.121 --> 22:36.554
Okay.

22:36.556 --> 22:38.489
Blood oxygen alarm, Mr. Mills.

22:38.491 --> 22:40.958
No, no, no, don't take the elevator
on the left, it's not working.

22:40.960 --> 22:43.694
- It's not working.
- Well, I'm sure I'll Figure it out.

22:43.696 --> 22:45.463
- See you later.
- Bye.

22:45.465 --> 22:47.698
You in here jibber-jabbering,
when he should be resting?

22:47.700 --> 22:49.767
- He's the jibber-jabberer.
- All right.

22:49.769 --> 22:51.102
You getting
your husband excited?

23:05.852 --> 23:08.119
Dad. Dad. No, no, no.
Don't get up.

23:08.121 --> 23:11.021
D-Dad, no, no, no. Dad. Andy!

23:11.023 --> 23:13.391
- I got to...
- No, no, no. What are you doing?

23:13.393 --> 23:15.426
- I got to take a crap!
- Okay, okay, easy.

23:15.428 --> 23:17.461
Hold on. I got to get behind you.
Over here.

23:17.463 --> 23:19.864
Dad. You doing good.
You're doing good.

23:19.866 --> 23:22.933
Relax, Dad. You're doing great.
Just relax for a second.

23:22.935 --> 23:27.605
Hey, Eddie, be careful of his PICC line,
that goes all the way inside his heart.

23:27.607 --> 23:29.707
- Yeah, be careful.
- I got to move, God damn it!

23:29.709 --> 23:31.008
We're moving. We're moving.

23:31.010 --> 23:32.710
Dad, I need you
to go slower. OK?

23:32.712 --> 23:34.545
Slower? If I go any slower,
I'll shit on your shoes.

23:34.547 --> 23:36.480
Wouldn't be the first time.

23:36.482 --> 23:36.950
I got to back up.

23:36.962 --> 23:38.149
I got you. I got you.
OK. I got you. Sorry.

23:38.151 --> 23:41.419
- OK. Stay with him.
- Stay with him.

23:41.421 --> 23:42.820
- I got it.
- Stay with him.

23:43.723 --> 23:45.589
All right, Dad. Get in there.

23:46.626 --> 23:48.159
I got it. God damn it.

23:48.161 --> 23:50.161
- I got it.
- All right.

23:50.163 --> 23:51.695
Hey, Dad.
It's one more step, Dad.

23:51.697 --> 23:53.431
- Get the hell out of here!
- Okay.

23:53.433 --> 23:55.166
What are you going to do?
Wipe my ass now?

23:55.168 --> 23:58.035
- God!
- Go on!

23:58.037 --> 24:00.838
- Yeah.
- There you go, Dad.

24:04.544 --> 24:06.043
That's my boy.

24:06.045 --> 24:07.178
- Hey!
- Just one more. Oh.

24:07.180 --> 24:08.646
Good morning, Eddie.

24:08.648 --> 24:10.014
- Hey.
- Mornin'. Mornin'.

24:10.016 --> 24:12.516
- How you guys doing?
- Good.

24:12.518 --> 24:15.219
- Phew. Hey, Dad.
- Ready? Ready?

24:15.221 --> 24:17.688
You look great. How you feeling?

24:17.690 --> 24:19.990
- I feel good.
- One more.

24:19.992 --> 24:22.193
You look wonderful, Dawn.

24:22.195 --> 24:25.095
- You do.
- Thank you.

24:25.097 --> 24:29.467
- Oh, sweetheart. Too much.
- Maybe too much sausage.

24:29.469 --> 24:32.770
OK. OK.

24:32.772 --> 24:34.839
Do I need to call
the nurse? You OK?

24:42.515 --> 24:44.715
- You all right?
- You all right?

24:44.717 --> 24:46.183
- All right.
- You want something?

24:46.185 --> 24:48.652
OK. You want something
to drink? Or you're OK?

24:50.089 --> 24:54.725
Oh, you boys... You guys are
really, really great to stay here

24:54.727 --> 24:57.027
and help with your father
like this, but...

24:57.029 --> 24:59.797
- Oh, it's no problem.
- Well, it's not really necessary.

24:59.799 --> 25:01.699
They have a great staff here.

25:01.701 --> 25:03.834
No, the staff here is
not exactly on the ball.

25:03.836 --> 25:07.571
- Well, we love the staff here.
- OK.

25:08.875 --> 25:10.241
You know what? I'm gonna pay you

25:10.243 --> 25:12.109
for all the gas you're using.

25:12.111 --> 25:15.679
- Dawn, you don't have to pay me for gas.
- No, I'm going to.

25:17.550 --> 25:19.984
You know, when I was your age,

25:19.986 --> 25:22.253
I was five years away
from retirement.

25:22.255 --> 25:25.890
I had a full pension
from BATA Shoes.

25:26.792 --> 25:28.993
I'm going to give you the $40.

25:28.995 --> 25:31.228
I'm not taking it.
I'm not taking the cash.

25:31.230 --> 25:32.596
- Take it, Eddie.
- I have my own money.

25:32.598 --> 25:34.865
Take the goddamn $40, will you?

25:34.867 --> 25:37.001
- See?
- OK.

25:37.003 --> 25:39.103
$40 is $40.

25:39.105 --> 25:40.105
Thank you.

25:41.741 --> 25:43.941
So, when are you flying back?

25:43.943 --> 25:47.745
Uh, I just got here.
I flew in yesterday.

25:47.747 --> 25:51.148
- Oh. Ooh. Wait a minute.
- Hold on.

25:51.150 --> 25:54.585
Uh, I got to take this.
I'll be right back.

25:54.587 --> 25:55.653
Be right back, sweetheart.

25:55.655 --> 25:57.021
- Yeah.
- I got him.

25:57.023 --> 25:58.122
- Can you do that?
- Yeah.

25:58.124 --> 25:59.823
- OK.
- Dad.

26:01.327 --> 26:02.927
So you done eating?

26:03.930 --> 26:06.347
Yeah.

26:06.348 --> 26:08.765
You want a little something else?
How about some rice pudding?

26:08.768 --> 26:11.001
You like rice... All right?
A little bit of rice pudding?

26:11.003 --> 26:12.069
- Yeah.
- Here you go.

26:15.741 --> 26:17.608
- Good stuff.
- Right.

26:21.914 --> 26:24.682
Always straight to dessert
for you, right?

26:26.786 --> 26:27.952
Here.

26:29.989 --> 26:32.156
- You like that?
- All right.

26:32.158 --> 26:34.625
That's good. You want to feed
yourself, or you want me to...

26:34.627 --> 26:36.760
- Hand me the goddamn...
- All right.

26:43.169 --> 26:46.937
- God.
- Sorry, Dad. Y-You OK?

26:46.939 --> 26:49.673
You OK? OK. He's choking.

26:49.675 --> 26:51.308
OK. Hold on.

26:51.310 --> 26:53.177
<i>Nursing station. Can I help you?</i>

26:53.179 --> 26:54.945
Yes, my father's choking
on something in here.

26:54.947 --> 26:56.847
- Dad.
- Oh, my God. What's happening?

26:56.849 --> 26:58.882
- Did you call the nurse?
- I did.

26:58.884 --> 27:01.085
- Could you help? Get in here.
- Oh, my God.

27:01.087 --> 27:03.754
God damn it.
Can I get a fucking nurse in here?

27:03.756 --> 27:06.190
- He can only swallow one thing at a time.
- My father's choking to death.

27:06.192 --> 27:08.792
Oh, my God.
Water goes straight to his lungs.

27:08.794 --> 27:11.295
What's happening here?

27:11.297 --> 27:13.731
I was only gone for a second.

27:13.733 --> 27:16.667
- How could you...
- Hang on, Dad.

27:16.669 --> 27:19.637
I'm not...

27:19.639 --> 27:22.272
These hospital staff
don't read anything.

27:22.274 --> 27:24.208
Help me lean him forward.

27:27.747 --> 27:30.814
- That is such a horrible thing to watch.
- I know. Would you please...

27:30.816 --> 27:33.150
Please, Diane,
get a hold of yourself.

27:33.152 --> 27:34.718
Dad, are you OK?

27:34.720 --> 27:37.254
Gentle breaths.
Breathing normally.

27:37.256 --> 27:38.822
Where is the nutritionist?

27:38.824 --> 27:40.658
Would you like to speak
to my supervisor?

27:40.660 --> 27:43.180
Very much. They brought the wrong food?
I mean, that's insanity.

27:45.030 --> 27:46.997
And I would like the
nutritionist up here immediately.

27:46.999 --> 27:48.332
- Right now!
- Thank you.

27:48.334 --> 27:49.900
It's not your fault.

27:49.902 --> 27:52.136
- Dad, you OK?
- Yeah, yeah.

27:52.138 --> 27:56.006
You're all right, sweetheart.
All right. OK, angel.

27:56.008 --> 27:59.943
You're OK. That was scary,
but you're OK, precious.

28:06.018 --> 28:10.187
Until he's re-evaluated,
we need to restrict all foods and liquids.

28:10.189 --> 28:13.424
So, what's that mean?
He can't eat or drink anything?

28:13.426 --> 28:15.959
Well, he's aspirated
into his lungs.

28:15.961 --> 28:18.762
That means...
means a feeding tube?

28:18.764 --> 28:21.699
No, no, no, no, Bob.
He didn't say that.

28:21.701 --> 28:24.068
As a last resort. Yes.

28:24.070 --> 28:26.437
Let's see how the
